        "response": {
          "output": "Here's a SQL query to find the top 10 customers by total revenue:\n\n```sql\nSELECT \n    c.id,\n    c.name,\n    SUM(o.amount) AS total_revenue\nFROM \n    customers c\n    INNER JOIN orders o ON c.id = o.customer_id\nGROUP BY \n    c.id, c.name\nORDER BY \n    total_revenue DESC\nLIMIT 10;\n```\n\nThis query:\n- Joins the customers and orders tables on the customer ID\n- Groups by customer to aggregate their orders\n- Sums the order amounts to calculate total revenue per customer\n- Orders by total revenue in descending order\n- Limits the results to the top 10\n\nIf you want to include customers with no orders (showing 0 revenue), use a LEFT JOIN instead:\n\n```sql\nSELECT \n    c.id,\n    c.name,\n    COALESCE(SUM(o.amount), 0) AS total_revenue\nFROM \n    customers c\n    LEFT JOIN orders o ON c.id = o.customer_id\nGROUP BY \n    c.id, c.name\nORDER BY \n    total_revenue DESC\nLIMIT 10;\n```",
