        "response": {
          "output": "```sql\nCREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY idx_users_email ON users(email);\n```\n\nThis uses PostgreSQL's `CONCURRENTLY` option, which allows the index to be built without blocking writes to the table. A few things to note:\n\n- The index creation will take longer than a standard `CREATE INDEX`\n- It requires more total work and takes more time to complete\n- It cannot be run inside a transaction block\n- If the build fails, it leaves behind an \"invalid\" index that should be dropped before retrying\n\nIf you need a unique index instead:\n\n```sql\nCREATE UNIQUE INDEX CONCURRENTLY idx_users_email ON users(email);\n```",
